01:17:32.360 --> 01:17:37.880
and I just want to say that
we have close to 200 editions

01:17:37.880 --> 01:17:44.420
at the library and it's
really, as Estévez said,

01:17:44.420 --> 01:17:48.670
it's a beautiful collection and
I just wish we had more moments

01:17:48.670 --> 01:17:53.140
like this where we can bring
them out, because it's just

01:17:53.140 --> 01:17:55.750
such a -- it's such a beauty.

01:17:55.750 --> 01:18:00.290
And this is one of many other
collections that the Library

01:18:00.290 --> 01:18:03.830
of Congress has, you
know, artist's books.

01:18:03.830 --> 01:18:07.880
So, there're many artit's books,
these are books that are again

01:18:07.880 --> 01:18:11.290
like these works of art,
so they're like more,

01:18:11.290 --> 01:18:14.780
they are more works of art
than, you know, than books,

01:18:14.780 --> 01:18:21.990
but they are just these
incredible creations,

01:18:21.990 --> 01:18:23.390
and these are all housed,

01:18:23.390 --> 01:18:26.570
and the custodial division
