decir algo más.

01:22:18.070 --> 01:22:19.370
&gt;&gt; Rolando Estévez:
¿Exactamente?

01:22:19.370 --> 01:22:23.890
&gt;&gt; Ruth Behar: So, you
want to know, we're trying

01:22:23.890 --> 01:22:26.550
to truly unpack the question.

01:22:26.550 --> 01:22:29.130
So, you wanted to connect the
love that he has for bookmaking

01:22:29.130 --> 01:22:30.430
with other kinds of love.

01:22:30.430 --> 01:22:33.990
&gt;&gt; Does he interact with
his family, friends,

01:22:33.990 --> 01:22:36.720
in the same way he does his art?

01:22:36.720 --> 01:22:40.860
It's apparent, when he -- when
you gave him the paint set,

01:22:40.860 --> 01:22:43.590
many years he gave
it back as art.

01:22:43.590 --> 01:22:46.150
I guess by -- it's kind
of a figurative question.

01:22:46.150 --> 01:22:49.350
You know, does he interact a
hundred percent as the artist

01:22:49.350 --> 01:22:52.560
with everyone he interacts with?

01:22:52.560 --> 01:22:58.820
Like, he would have hundreds of
people wanting to be his friend.

01:22:58.820 --> 01:23:01.180
They would be like,
"Write me a letter.

01:23:01.180 --> 01:23:02.480
I love you.

01:23:02.480 --> 01:23:03.780
This is art.

01:23:03.780 --> 01:23:05.080
You know, just to touch
or be near is art."

01:23:05.080 --> 01:23:06.580
&gt;&gt; Ruth Behar: Que si tú traes
todas estas formas con todos tus

01:23:06.580 --> 01:23:09.080
amigos y seres queridos, porque
has hecho unos libros bellos,

01:23:09.080 --> 01:23:10.380
por ejemplo, conmigo,

01:23:10.380 --> 01:23:12.070
porque todo el mundo va
a querer ser tu amigo.

01:23:12.070 --> 01:23:14.460
[ Risa ]

01:23:14.460 --> 01:23:17.160
&gt;&gt; Rolando Estévez:
La cosa está en --

01:23:17.160 --> 01:23:19.600
la expresión de un artista es --

01:23:19.600 --> 01:23:21.240
o sea, tiene que
salir del interior.

01:23:21.240 --> 01:23:22.540
Ahí nada más está todo.

01:23:22.540 --> 01:23:26.460
Y cuando tú combinas lo que está
aquí en tu energía con lo que

01:23:26.460 --> 01:23:31.400
está en tu cerebro y convocas
al acto intelectual y al acto

01:23:31.400 --> 01:23:36.740
emocional, ahí ya todo se
hace -- se condensa, ¿no?

01:23:36.740 --> 01:23:38.040
¿Entiendes?

01:23:38.040 --> 01:23:39.340
&gt;&gt; Ruth Behar: Sí.

01:23:39.340 --> 01:23:41.630
So, the energy has to come from
inside and that's always kind

01:23:41.630 --> 01:23:46.850
of a combination of feelings,
and intellectual concepts,

01:23:46.850 --> 01:23:49.140
and all of that kind
of gets condensed

01:23:49.140 --> 01:23:51.950
into artistic expression.

01:23:51.950 --> 01:23:55.560
&gt;&gt; Rolando Estévez: Y esto que
decía de la comunicación con los

01:23:55.560 --> 01:23:59.160
autores, a veces, tiene que
ser hasta un poco espiritista,

01:23:59.160 --> 01:24:02.340
porque hasta con los Muertos,

01:24:02.340 --> 01:24:05.800
tú logras crear a través
de lo que han escrito,

01:24:05.800 --> 01:24:07.620
lo que te han dicho,
saber de ellos,

01:24:07.620 --> 01:24:10.220
yo me he preguntado
muchas veces:

01:24:10.220 --> 01:24:12.450
"¿Le gustaría este
libro a Frida Kahlo?

01:24:12.450 --> 01:24:13.750
¿Le gustaría?

01:24:13.750 --> 01:24:15.050
¿Le hubiera gustado?

01:24:15.050 --> 01:24:16.350
¿Le gustará?"

01:24:16.350 --> 01:24:17.650
Si está en alguna parte.

01:24:17.650 --> 01:24:20.750
&gt;&gt; Ruth Behar: So, it's a deep
communication with the person

01:24:20.750 --> 01:24:23.820
that you are writing
about, the author of a text,

01:24:23.820 --> 01:24:26.470
and it might be Frida Kahlo,
who is no longer alive

01:24:26.470 --> 01:24:30.080
and he asks himself, "Would
Frida like this book?"

01:24:30.080 --> 01:24:33.660
So, this kind of this very
deep communication that goes

01:24:33.660 --> 01:24:37.830
on between himself as a
maker of artist's books

01:24:37.830 --> 01:24:42.120
and then the author of the
work that he's writing about

01:24:42.120 --> 01:24:44.990
and finding that kind of
deep level of communication.

01:24:44.990 --> 01:24:47.180
Yeah.

01:24:47.180 --> 01:24:49.820
&gt;&gt; Marie Arana: I want
